PART 2 — THE NEW FEATURE I AM ADDING (the RAG upgrade)
============================================================

I am adding a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline so the chatbot answers from real campus discussions plus live web data, instead of being a generic LLM.

AI provider for the RAG pipeline:
- GOOGLE GEMINI (not OpenAI, not Groq)
- Embeddings: models/text-embedding-004  (768 dimensions, NOT 1536)
- Generation:  gemini-1.5-flash
- Library:     google-generativeai
- API key env var: GEMINI_API_KEY (free at https://aistudio.google.com)

Vector DB: MongoDB Atlas Vector Search (the same Mongo cluster the rest of the app uses). NOT Pinecone, NOT Weaviate. Atlas has native vector search via the $vectorSearch aggregation stage.

Web search (optional): Tavily (https://tavily.com), free tier, used only when the query is about current/recent info or when no campus discussions match.

ARCHITECTURE:

The RAG pipeline lives entirely in a NEW Python FastAPI service called "rag-service" running on port 8001. It owns:
- Gemini embeddings (text-embedding-004)
- Gemini generation (gemini-1.5-flash)
- MongoDB $vectorSearch via pymongo (its own Mongo connection, separate from Node’s Mongoose)
- Tavily web search via tavily-python

The Node backend stays as the user-facing API. When a chat request comes in, Node calls Python at POST /chat. Python does the full pipeline and returns the answer. If Python is down or fails, Node falls back to the existing Groq logic so the app never breaks.

Flow on chat request:
  user → React → POST /api/v1/chat/chat (Node)
       → POST http://localhost:8001/chat (Python)
           1. Gemini embed_query(message)
           2. Mongo $vectorSearch over discussions collection
           3. If no campus hits OR query mentions "latest/2024/2025/recent/etc", call Tavily
           4. Gemini gemini-1.5-flash generates the final reply using one of 4 prompt templates (based on whether campus/web context is available)
       → returns { response, ragUsed, sourcesCount, webUsed } → back to React
       → ChatBot.jsx shows "✓ Based on N campus discussions" under bot replies when ragUsed=true

Flow on discussion creation (indexing side):
  user → React → POST /api/v1/discussion/ (Node)
       → Mongoose creates the document
       → Node fires-and-forgets POST http://localhost:8001/embed
       → Python generates Gemini embedding from {title, content, tags, category} and writes it back to the same Mongo document via pymongo

Discussion categories (new enum on the Discussion model):
  ["competitive-programming", "interview-experience", "placement-prep",
   "tech-discussion", "career-advice", "general"]
  Default: "general". Category filter tabs added to the discussion page.

Rate limit: 20 chat messages per hour per user, keyed on req.user._id (uses express-rate-limit).

